blockers.resolution:
Use UNIX_MINUTE * 7 (seven minutes) as the maxAge for the getDefault pre-check inside createDefaultVault. This blocker requires changes to TWO files — both types.ts and PassBridgeFactory.ts must be modified.

Step 1 — packages/pass/lib/bridge/types.ts: Update the PassBridge interface vault section. Remove the hadVault callback parameter from getDefault. Change its type to MaxAgeMemoizedFn<() => Promise<Share<ShareType.Vault> | undefined>> (note: inner function type has NO parameters; return type includes | undefined). Add createDefaultVault(): Promise<Share<ShareType.Vault>> to the vault object.

Step 2 — packages/pass/lib/bridge/PassBridgeFactory.ts, refactor getDefault: The existing getDefault currently both resolves AND creates a vault, and accepts a hadVaultCallback parameter. Remove the hadVaultCallback parameter and all vault creation logic from the inner function. The inner function must take NO arguments: maxAgeMemoize(async () => { ... }). It should resolve the oldest active owned writable vault and return it, or return undefined (via return first(candidates)). Import UNIX_MINUTE from '@proton/pass/utils/time/constants'.

Step 3 — packages/pass/lib/bridge/PassBridgeFactory.ts, add createDefaultVault: Add the method inside the vault object using method syntax (NOT arrow function) because it calls this.getDefault() which requires correct this binding:

async createDefaultVault() {
    const defaultVault = await this.getDefault({ maxAge: UNIX_MINUTE * 7 });
    if (defaultVault) {
        return defaultVault;
    }
    const newVault = await createVault({
        content: {
            name: 'Personal',
            description: 'Personal vault (created from Mail)',
            display: {},
        },
    });
    return newVault;
}

Use exactly the constant expression UNIX_MINUTE * 7.

CRITICAL — MaxAgeMemoizedFn behavior: The memoization wrapper intercepts { maxAge } from the call-site and passes nothing to the inner function. When createDefaultVault calls this.getDefault({ maxAge: UNIX_MINUTE * 7 }), the wrapper extracts maxAge and forwards zero arguments to the inner async () => { ... }. Do NOT add an options/maxAge parameter to getDefault's inner function signature.
